result.execSummary:
The defendant David Gutierrez was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Battery by Prisoners, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.20(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

11:09 a.m.  State by ADA Lisa Vanden Branden.  Defendant present, in custody, with Attorney Reisha Mitchell.

Court recites the agreement - defendant plea to count 1 - dismiss repeater.  DRI count 2.  ADA concurs.  Attorney Mitchell concurs.  Defendant concurs.

Court goes over plea questionnaire with the defendant.  Court goes over constitutional rights with the defendant - waived.  Court goes over the elements of the offense.  Court instructs regarding the maximum penalties.  Court instructs regarding deportation.  Court instructs regarding felony prohibitions.  

Defendant enters a plea of NO CONTEST to count 1.  Court finds the plea is made freely, voluntarily, intelligently, and understandingly.  Court finds there is a factual basis to support the plea.  Court finds the defendant guilty on count 1 - dismisses the repeater - orders a judgment of conviction be entered today.  Court DRI count 2.  ADA confirms compliance with any victim/witness rights.  Sentencing argument by ADA.  Sentencing argument by Attorney Mitchell.  No statement by the defendant.

Court sentences the defendant to 120 days county jail - consecutive to any other sentence the defendant is currently serving - commence immediately - no huber.
Pay court costs - 60 days to pay or payment plan.

Court adjourned at 11:17 a.m.
Plea/sentencing hearing on June 3, 2014 at 11:00 am.

1:27 p.m.   State by ADA Lisa Vanden Branden.  Defendant present, in custody, with Attorney Reisha Mitchell.

Statement by Attorney Mitchell - defendant waives right to a preliminary hearing - defendant concurs.  Court instructs defendant of his right to a preliminary hearing.  Defendant waives his right to a preliminary hearing.  Court accepts the waiver and binds the defendant over for trial.

ADA files an Information with the court and provides a copy to Attorney Mitchell.  Attorney Mitchell confirms receipt of the Information - waives reading - enters a plea of NOT GUILTY on behalf of the defendant.  Court makes statement regarding the maximum penalties.

Court directs Plea/Sentencing to be held in approximately thirty days.

Court adjourned at 1:29 p.m.
Preliminary hearing on April 22, 2014 at 01:00 pm.
Defendant is to complete processing with the Green Lake County Sheriff's Department.
Preliminary hearing on April 15, 2014 at 11:00 am.
Defendant is to complete processing with the Green Lake County Sheriff's Department.

9:08 a.m.  Defendant in custody and present in court without counsel.  Kyle Sargent for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant confirms receipt of the criminal complaint and waives reading. Court instructs the defendant of the maximum penalty on each count and as repeater.  Court finds probable cause.  Court instructs defendant of his/her right to an attorney.  DA makes bond recommendation.  Court sets bond at $500.00 signature bond and condition of:  Defendant is to complete processing with the Green Lake County Sheriff's Department..  Court instructs defendant regarding his/her right to a preliminary hearing.  Defendant does not waive the time limits.  Court will set for Status Hearing and Preliminary Hearing after.

Court adjourned at 9:10 a.m.
